{"pageProps":{"tutorial":{"title":"CSS Borders","slug":"css-borders","subject":"CSS","category":"Web Development","level":"Beginner","estimated_read_time":"10 mins","prerequisites":["CSS Box Model (Concept)"],"learning_objectives":["Learn border-style","Learn border-width","Learn border-color","Learn border-radius","Learn border sides (top, right, bottom, left)","Learn the border shorthand"],"theory":"The CSS border properties allow you to specify the style, width, and color of an element's border.\n\n*   `border-style`: Required. Specifies the kind of border (solid, dotted, dashed, double, etc.).\n*   `border-width`: Width of the border (px, em, thick, thin).\n*   `border-color`: Color of the border.\n*   `border-radius`: Adds rounded corners.\n*   `border`: Shorthand property.","syntax":"/* Shorthand */\np {\n  border: 5px solid red;\n}\n\n/* Individual Sides */\ndiv {\n  border-bottom: 2px solid black;\n}","examples":[{"code":"div {\n  border: 2px solid black;\n  border-radius: 10px;\n}","output":"A box with a 2px black outline and rounded corners.","explanation":"border-radius creates the curved edges."}],"common_mistakes":[{"mistake":"Defining width/color without style","correction":"`border-style` is mandatory. If not set, the border won't appear.","example":"WRONG: border-width: 5px; (Invisible)\nCORRECT: border: 5px solid;"}],"interview_questions":[{"question":"How do you create a circle using CSS borders?","answer":"Set width and height to be equal (a square) and `border-radius: 50%`.","difficulty":"Medium"}],"practice_problems":[{"problem":"Add a solid red border only to the bottom of a <p> tag.","hint":"Use the specific side property.","solution":"p {\n  border-bottom: 1px solid red;\n}","difficulty":"Easy"}],"real_world_use_cases":[{"scenario":"Input Fields","description":"Form inputs use borders to define the typing area. Changing border color on focus indicates activity.","code":"input:focus { border-color: blue; }"}],"exam_notes":["Border style 'none'